title: Youth unemployment rate in Zambia in 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Youth unemployment rate. In total the number of data points it has is 21.
In general Youth unemployment rate has fallen over the Year.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2008 and 2009.
Maximum Youth unemployment rate, about 28.26 was reported at Year 2005
Minimum Youth unemployment rate about 15.94 was reached at Year 2019
